import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = data.plot.bar(x='state', y='rate', legend=False)
    avg_rate = data['rate'].mean()
    plt.axhline(y=avg_rate, color='r', linestyle='-', label=f'Average: {avg_rate:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the average obesity rate across all states?")
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['rate'], bins=20, edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Obesity Rates')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the distribution of obesity rates across all states?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    us_map = gpd.read_file('https://eric.clst.org/assets/wiki/uploads/Stuff/gz_2010_us_040_00_5m.json')
    data['id'] = data['id'].astype(str)
    merged_data = us_map.set_index('STATE').join(data.set_index('id'))

    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = merged_data.plot(column='rate', cmap='coolwarm', legend=True, edgecolor='black', linewidth=0.5)
    ax.set_title('Which state has the highest obesity rate?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_axis_off()

    max_rate_state = data.loc[data['rate'].idxmax()]['state']
    max_rate = data['rate'].max()
    ax.annotate(f"{max_rate_state}: {max_rate:.2f}", xy=(0.5, 0.1), xycoords='axes fraction', fontsize=12, color='black', ha='center')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    x = data['state']
    y = data['rate']
    
    plt.scatter(x, y)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Obesity Rate')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between obesity rates and state population?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['id'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['rate'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.axhline(data['rate'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['rate'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    
    plt.title("What is the trend of obesity rates over time?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
